The paper deals with the planarity of graphs and their embeddings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of generalized planar dual graphs suggests a connection to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The tight bounds on the density of maximal NIC-planar graphs and the recognition problem suggest a connection to graph theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.DC).
